Verification Workflow:
Create a new scratch directory and initialize a basic configuration file to test the setup:

1. Create a main.tf file:

hcl
provider "aws" {                        #resource is a provider, parameter is aws
  region = "us-east-1"                  #argument is region
}

resource "aws_vpc" "test_vpc" {          #to create - resource, parameter is aws_vpc, name is test_vpc
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/16"             #argument is cidr_block
  tags = {
    Name = "Terraform-Test-VPC"
  }
}

2. Run the initialization workflow sequentially:

terraform init    # Downloads the AWS provider plugin
terraform plan    # Shows the execution blueprint
terraform apply   # Executes and deploys the infrastructure resource

In Terraform, arguments are inputs you define to configure a resource, while attributes are data points generated by that resource after 
it is created. Arguments are assigned with an equals sign (=) in your configuration files, whereas attributes are read-only properties of
the resulting object that can be used elsewhere in your code.

